<p><a href="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-24-hellys-theorem.jpg"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-24-hellys-theorem.jpg" alt="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Helly%27s_theorem.svg" width="1024" height="392" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-71301" srcset="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-24-hellys-theorem.jpg 1024w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-24-hellys-theorem-600x230.jpg 600w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-24-hellys-theorem-300x115.jpg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>
<p>In a family of convex sets in the Euclidean plane, if the intersection of each triple is non-empty, then the intersection of the whole collection is non-empty.</p>
<p>Discovered by Austrian mathematician Eduard Helly in 1913.</p>
